modules.description: Provides operations to define and manipulate comment structure elements, including style classifications, reference types, and tagged text annotations. Works with nested lists of text elements, reference identifiers, and metadata tags. Used to represent and process documentation comments with structured formatting and cross-references.

Provides functions to extract error messages from structured error types. Works with position, location, parser_error, lexer_error, and error types to represent and retrieve detailed error information. Used to generate human-readable error outputs during parsing and lexical analysis.

Parses ocamldoc-style comments into structured data, extracting tags, descriptions, and annotations. Works with strings representing comment blocks and produces abstract syntax trees. Used to generate documentation headers or analyze code comments for static analysis tools.

Handles structured comment elements and error information, enabling the creation, manipulation, and extraction of formatted documentation and error details. Supports nested text lists, reference identifiers, metadata tags, and error types with positional data. Allows for processing of annotated comments and retrieval of detailed error messages. Can generate styled documentation and diagnostic outputs with cross-references and location-specific error descriptions.
